As mentioned in the comments - you could just store the numbers in a shuffled list and just pop values off.  This gets a little weird because you can only pop 75 values until you need to replenish the list and your range of possible values is stored up front in memory.  An alternative approach is to maintain a Set of seen values 

    Set&lt;Integer&gt; seenValues = new HashSet&lt;&gt;();

and add values to the Set as you serve them up and of course check to see if the value you are currently serving is already in the `seenValues`.

