You can use LocalDateTime if your minSdkVersion is 26 (Android 8.0) or higher [1]. Otherwise, you can use [core library desugaring][2].

```
android {
    defaultConfig {
        // Required when setting minSdkVersion to 20 or lower
        multiDexEnabled true
    }

    compileOptions {
        // Flag to enable support for the new language APIs
        coreLibraryDesugaringEnabled true
        // Sets Java compatibility to Java 8
        sourceCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
        targetCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
    }
}

dependencies {
    coreLibraryDesugaring &#39;com.android.tools:desugar_jdk_libs:1.1.5&#39;
}
```


  [1]: https://developer.android.com/reference/java/time/LocalDateTime
  [2]: https://developer.android.com/studio/write/java8-support#library-desugaring

